ORANGE COUNTY EARNINGS 
ICN Biomedicals Inc. The Costa Mesa-based maker of medical instruments and test 
kits said net income for the first quarter reached a record $1.9 million, 
compared to $942,000 reported for the comparable period last year. Sales for 
the quarter ended Feb. 28 rose to nearly $33 million from $12.9 million. The 
company said the gains in revenue and earnings for the first quarter were 
attributable to continued strength of its base business as well as the 
consolidation into its operations of Flow Laboratories, which it acquired in 
November. 
